WEBVTT

00:00:00.720 --> 00:00:07.719
Welcome! This month's program will help us show love and respect in marriage.

00:00:07.719 --> 00:00:14.720
Here are a few highlights. Is your marriage drained because your spouse opposes the truth?

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:19.719
We'll see how Alexandru's love and patience promoted peace in his marriage

00:00:19.719 --> 00:00:24.719
and ultimately moved his wife, Dharina, to serve Jehovah.

00:00:24.719 --> 00:00:29.719
We'll learn how Claudius Johnson dealt with changing circumstances

00:00:29.719 --> 00:00:36.719
and our new original song reminds us of the joys of marriage based on Bible principles.

00:00:36.719 --> 00:00:40.719
This is JW Broadcasting for March 2021.

00:00:40.719 --> 00:01:06.500
Jehovah Design Marriage is a beautiful and rewarding relationship between a husband and a wife.

00:01:06.500 --> 00:01:12.500
When a husband and wife fulfill their God-given roles and they treat each other with love and respect,

00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:16.500
their marriage is a wonderful and intimate friendship.

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:24.500
A marriage that has good patterns, shaped by Jehovah's principles, looks like this well-balanced family circle.

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:30.500
But if a married couple over time has set bad patterns in how they deal with each other,

00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:35.500
this is often the result. The life's going to be a bit rough for them.

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:40.500
Let's consider what Jehovah says about the roles of husband and wife

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:46.500
and then discuss how love and respect are real keys to a happy marriage.

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:51.500
So what roles did Jehovah give to the man and woman in marriage?

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:55.500
Well, Jehovah places the husband as head of the family.

00:01:55.500 --> 00:02:01.500
Ephesians 523 says a husband is head of his wife.

00:02:01.500 --> 00:02:05.500
So that means the husband makes final decisions for the family

00:02:05.500 --> 00:02:09.500
and his decisions reflect his love for his wife, his children,

00:02:09.500 --> 00:02:14.500
and his understanding of their spiritual, physical, and emotional needs.

00:02:14.500 --> 00:02:22.500
At 1 Corinthians 11 and verse 3, we get a sense, though, of how Jehovah feels about the husband's role.

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:26.500
And as we read this together, I want you to imagine Jehovah saying to husbands,

00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:33.500
yes, your head of the family, but I want you to know that the head of every man is the Christ

00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:37.500
and in turn the head of a woman is the man.

00:02:37.500 --> 00:02:41.500
Sounds a lot like a father-in-law speaking to the groom.

00:02:41.500 --> 00:02:48.500
You can marry my daughter, but you better treat her good because you're responsible to me.

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:51.500
Well, Jehovah is giving a very clear message for husbands.

00:02:51.500 --> 00:02:57.500
Jehovah will hold you accountable to him for how you treat your wife.

00:02:57.500 --> 00:03:01.500
It's something for us husbands to think about, isn't it?

00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:04.500
Well, what about the role of a wife?

00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:08.500
Jehovah assigned wives as a beloved partner to her husband.

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:11.500
And as partners, they can discuss important family matters

00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:15.500
and work together to make their marriage a success.

00:03:15.500 --> 00:03:18.500
Jehovah placed the woman under the headship of the man,

00:03:18.500 --> 00:03:23.500
and as such, her role is to be in subjection to him.

00:03:23.500 --> 00:03:27.500
At Ephesians 5 and verse 22, it says,

00:03:27.500 --> 00:03:32.500
Let wives be in subjection to their husbands as to the Lord.

00:03:32.500 --> 00:03:36.500
Subjection. Set a certain way, it almost sounds bad.

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:38.500
You have to be in subjection.

00:03:38.500 --> 00:03:44.500
But is the subjection of a Christian wife to a Christian husband a bad thing? No.

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:49.500
See, subjection as described in the Bible is not about being subservient.

00:03:49.500 --> 00:03:52.500
It's about her role in the marriage.

00:03:53.500 --> 00:03:57.500
Your partners, each with a beautiful role to fulfill.

00:03:57.500 --> 00:04:01.500
We could illustrate it with watching a couple ice skating.

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:04.500
As they move gracefully across the ice,

00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:10.500
Do you think to yourself, how come they never let her hold him over her head?

00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:13.500
Well, no, you look at him, you look at her,

00:04:13.500 --> 00:04:17.500
it's obvious who should hold who over their head.

00:04:17.500 --> 00:04:21.500
Well, just as we admire and respect a woman's role as an ice skating partner,

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:26.500
a husband deeply loves and appreciates his wife's role as his partner

00:04:26.500 --> 00:04:30.500
as they work gracefully together to make their marriage a success.

00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:35.500
Well, now that we briefly reviewed the roles for husbands and wives,

00:04:35.500 --> 00:04:42.500
let's read together a key scriptural principle at Ephesians 5 and verse 33

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:49.500
that shows how Jehovah wants husbands and wives to fulfill their roles in marriage.

00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:53.500
Ephesians 5 and verse 33.

00:04:53.500 --> 00:04:57.500
Each one of you must love his wife as he does himself.

00:04:57.500 --> 00:05:03.500
On the other hand, the wife should have deep respect for her husband.

00:05:03.500 --> 00:05:08.500
Well, the obvious message in the Scripture is that husbands should love their wives

00:05:08.500 --> 00:05:11.500
and wives should respect their husbands.

00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:18.500
However, there's another way to look at the Scripture and learn something about husbands and wives.

00:05:18.500 --> 00:05:22.500
Jehovah God is telling us what each mate needs.

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:26.500
Men need respect and women need love.

00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:32.500
Now, this is not to say that men don't need love and women don't need to be respected.

00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:37.500
However, it does mean that men tend to emphasize respect and status

00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:43.500
and women often emphasize intimacy, connection, and love.

00:05:44.500 --> 00:05:52.500
This perfect principle can help us to understand why our husband or wife may act or feel a certain way.

00:05:52.500 --> 00:05:57.500
Now, this difference in emphasis affects many areas of married life.

00:05:57.500 --> 00:06:10.500
Let's consider three examples of how this powerful scriptural principle of love and respect can give us insight into how a husband and wife talk to each other,

00:06:10.500 --> 00:06:15.500
how they solve problems, and how they act in the company of others.

00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:19.500
Let's consider our first example, how they talk to each other.

00:06:19.500 --> 00:06:23.500
Now, since a wife's emphasis is on being loved,

00:06:23.500 --> 00:06:29.500
her conversations often stress friendship and connection when she talks to her husband.

00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:35.500
She's eager to share the details of her life with him and in this way become closer to him.

00:06:35.500 --> 00:06:40.500
She wants him in turn to share with her the details of his day in life.

00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:50.500
Husbands, your wife feels loved when you learn to communicate with her in a way that tells her you truly care about her.

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:55.500
She places great emphasis on conversation and sharing her life with you,

00:06:55.500 --> 00:06:59.500
and likewise you sharing your life with her.

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:05.500
For example, a wife tells her husband about something that happened to her that day.

00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:12.500
He grows impatient with the story and interrupts or changes the subject or offers a quick solution.

00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:14.500
How does she feel?

00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:20.500
Why can't he listen to the whole story? Has he lost interest in me?

00:07:20.500 --> 00:07:26.500
It's important that husbands give their wives their full attention as they speak.

00:07:27.500 --> 00:07:32.500
After a long day at work, his mind may be focused on events that happen to him that day,

00:07:32.500 --> 00:07:40.500
and he may, without realizing it, feel that the events or conversation of his wife aren't on important subjects.

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:46.500
So he may be inclined to play down the events in her life as unimportant or trivial,

00:07:46.500 --> 00:07:52.500
while events he talks about are substantial and important because they happen to him.

00:07:52.500 --> 00:07:56.500
Well, such a feeling over time can truly discourage a wife.

00:07:56.500 --> 00:08:05.500
A husband's disinterest in her stories and events of her life feels a lot like disinterest in her.

00:08:05.500 --> 00:08:10.500
The advice of Proverbs 20 and verse 5 is good for husbands.

00:08:10.500 --> 00:08:14.500
It says, the thoughts of a man, or we could say in this case,

00:08:14.500 --> 00:08:21.500
women's heart are like deep waters, but the discerning man draws them out.

00:08:21.500 --> 00:08:24.500
That's great advice for husbands.

00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:29.500
Husbands, when you draw your wife out, let her speak from her heart.

00:08:29.500 --> 00:08:34.500
That's an indication of great love and affection for your dear wife.

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:39.500
Men, on the other hand, often view conversation differently.

00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:42.500
A husband comes home and his wife asks, how was your day?

00:08:42.500 --> 00:08:45.500
He says, it was okay, nothing special.

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:48.500
But later than at night, when they're with a group of friends,

00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:51.500
he tells a story about what happened at work.

00:08:51.500 --> 00:08:57.500
And she wonders, well, why didn't he tell me that when I asked about his day?

00:08:57.500 --> 00:09:03.500
Well, since a man's emphasis is on respect, they often use conversation

00:09:03.500 --> 00:09:06.500
to establish respect and status with others.

00:09:06.500 --> 00:09:09.500
A husband may feel that his wife already respects him,

00:09:09.500 --> 00:09:13.500
so there's no need to tell her the story.

00:09:13.500 --> 00:09:17.500
Wives, you can encourage your husband to share his life with you

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.500
by being interested in his work and activities.

00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:24.500
If you tell him, don't talk to me about all that work stuff with me,

00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:26.500
he won't.

00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:29.500
And you'll cut yourself off from a part of his life.

00:09:29.500 --> 00:09:32.500
Show him you're proud of what he does to support the family.

00:09:32.500 --> 00:09:36.500
Be interested in what happened to him, how he feels about things

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:38.500
or challenges that he overcame.

00:09:38.500 --> 00:09:41.500
While you may not find his work all that interesting,

00:09:41.500 --> 00:09:45.500
remember, it is important to him.

00:09:45.500 --> 00:09:50.500
Let's consider our second example, how they solve problems.

00:09:50.500 --> 00:09:53.500
Now, I want you to imagine a husband and wife, they're in a car,

00:09:53.500 --> 00:09:56.500
they're looking for an address, and they're lost.

00:09:56.500 --> 00:10:00.500
And the wife suggests that they ask someone for directions.

00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:04.500
She's thinking, why won't he ask?

00:10:04.500 --> 00:10:08.500
He's thinking, why can't she just let me find it?

00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:12.500
You see, since the man's emphasis is on respect,

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:16.500
he's trying to avoid looking lost to a stranger.

00:10:16.500 --> 00:10:21.500
The act of asking someone else for directions may make him feel

00:10:21.500 --> 00:10:24.500
like he's in a lower position.

00:10:24.500 --> 00:10:28.500
Finding their way is a challenge to him, and he wants to show his wife

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:30.500
that he can find it on his own.

00:10:30.500 --> 00:10:33.500
For the woman, such an idea may not come to mind.

00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:37.500
She may view it as a simple interchange between them and a stranger.

00:10:37.500 --> 00:10:41.500
They may get help in directions, and they find out where they're going.

00:10:41.500 --> 00:10:46.500
At 1 Corinthians chapter 7 and verse 33, Jehovah tells us,

00:10:46.500 --> 00:10:52.500
but the married man is anxious, how he may gain the approval of his wife.

00:10:52.500 --> 00:10:57.500
Wives your husband is anxious to have your approval and respect.

00:10:57.500 --> 00:11:01.500
But on balance, husbands have to be careful that an emphasis on respect

00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:04.500
doesn't become unreasonable.

00:11:04.500 --> 00:11:08.500
He won't hurt us to ask for directions or help at times.

00:11:08.500 --> 00:11:12.500
On the other hand, a wife needs to be careful that she doesn't show impatience

00:11:12.500 --> 00:11:18.500
by her words or tone as her husband works his way through a problem.

00:11:18.500 --> 00:11:22.500
A wife who clearly understands her husband's desire to solve problems

00:11:22.500 --> 00:11:27.500
for the family will understand his actions and will do her part to support him,

00:11:27.500 --> 00:11:30.500
even in the little things around the home.

00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:35.500
Now, this support in the little areas of life builds his confidence in her support

00:11:35.500 --> 00:11:42.500
and can be a major factor in whether a husband takes the lead in larger matters.

00:11:42.500 --> 00:11:48.500
Our third and final example, how they act in front of others.

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:51.500
Have you ever seen a couple where one of them is telling a story

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:56.500
and the other is constantly correcting the details?

00:11:56.500 --> 00:11:59.500
Or the husband is trying to give some direction

00:11:59.500 --> 00:12:03.500
and the wife corrects or challenges the direction?

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:09.500
Or the husband is telling others some unflattering story that hurts his wife's feelings.

00:12:09.500 --> 00:12:15.500
How can Ephesians 533 help a wife in these situations?

00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:18.500
Well, since a husband's emphasis is on respect,

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:24.500
he'll be much more sensitive to comments his wife may make in front of others.

00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:31.500
It can hurt a husband deeply when his wife openly challenges him in front of others.

00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:37.500
Proverbs 31 and verse 12 has this advice for wives.

00:12:37.500 --> 00:12:43.500
She rewards him with good, not bad, all the days of her life.

00:12:43.500 --> 00:12:48.500
So when in public or when others are around, even close family and children,

00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:52.500
try not to openly disagree with him, correct him,

00:12:52.500 --> 00:12:55.500
or attempt to take over what he's doing.

00:12:55.500 --> 00:13:02.500
How you speak to your husband in front of others is a great way to show your deep respect for him.

00:13:02.500 --> 00:13:08.850
It also builds respect for him and others, including any children in the family.

00:13:08.850 --> 00:13:14.850
Well, how can Ephesians 533 help a husband act in front of others?

00:13:14.850 --> 00:13:22.850
Well, when in public, husbands will want to act like the husband in Proverbs 31 and verse 28.

00:13:22.850 --> 00:13:27.850
It says her husband rises up and praises her.

00:13:27.850 --> 00:13:34.850
It's common today for husbands to make fun of, or even say demeaning things about their wives.

00:13:34.850 --> 00:13:38.850
But since a wife places so much emphasis on connection and friendship,

00:13:38.850 --> 00:13:43.850
she can really be hurt when demeaning remarks are said to get a laugh.

00:13:43.850 --> 00:13:45.850
It makes her feel awful.

00:13:45.850 --> 00:13:51.850
Husbands, your wife considers you her best friend, the one she shares everything with.

00:13:51.850 --> 00:13:56.850
If you break that trust, she feels unloved and hurt.

00:13:56.850 --> 00:14:01.850
Now, the best time to bring matters to each other's attention is when you're in private,

00:14:01.850 --> 00:14:07.850
or if needed, when you can talk in such a way that others cannot hear what's being said.

00:14:07.850 --> 00:14:17.320
In this way, a wife shows deep respect for her husband, and the husband shows his love for his wife.

00:14:17.320 --> 00:14:27.320
So in review, we've considered just three situations that the principle of love and respect can help us to have a successful marriage.

00:14:27.320 --> 00:14:36.320
How husband and wife talk to each other, how they solve problems, and how they act in the company of others.

00:14:36.320 --> 00:14:41.320
A good marriage is hard work. How was your marriage?

00:14:41.320 --> 00:14:47.320
Would you say that you've developed good patterns or bad patterns in dealing with each other?

00:14:47.320 --> 00:14:54.320
When was the last time you talked as a couple about love and respect for each other?

00:14:54.320 --> 00:15:03.320
Jehovah's perfect advice at Ephesians 533 can help the marriage of two imperfect people.

00:15:03.320 --> 00:15:09.320
In just a few words in this verse, Jehovah is sharing with us a key principle of how he designed marriage.

00:15:09.320 --> 00:15:14.320
He's telling us what each needs and places emphasis on.

00:15:14.320 --> 00:15:21.320
Husbands put emphasis on being respected, and wives put emphasis on being loved.

00:15:21.320 --> 00:15:27.320
And this principle forms a key part of the divine pattern for marriage.

00:15:27.320 --> 00:15:32.320
If you want your marriage to operate as Jehovah designed,

00:15:32.320 --> 00:15:40.320
then work hard to apply his perfect principle of love and respect in your marriage.

00:15:40.320 --> 00:15:48.429
Why can we be confident that Bible principles for husbands and wives work?

00:15:48.429 --> 00:15:52.429
Because they've worked for Jehovah's people in the past.

